description.narrative: In 2021, health emergency response was the principal focus of UNICEF Health program on covering the various emergency crises (Earthquake, COVID-19, urban violence/IDPs, Scabies) which hit the country and paralyzed the healthcare system. In emergency situation UNICEF has allowed approximately 192,000 children and women to receive essential healthcare services in UNICEF supported facilities and through mobile clinics. UNICEF also played a central role in the introduction of the anti-COVID-19 vaccine to the country through the COVAX initiative, also promoting demand generation and ensuring the appropriate cold chain; where around 125,000 people are already vaccinated against COVID-19 across the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
